    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>We present an in-depth analysis of data from drive through testing stations using rapid antigen detection tests (RDT\u2019s), RT-PCR and virus culture, to assess the ability of RDT\u2019s to detect infectious cases. We show that the detection limits of five commercially available RDT\u2019s differ considerably, impacting the translation into the detection of infectious cases. We recommend careful fit-for-purpose testing before implementation of antigen RDT\u2019s in routine testing algorithms as part of the COVID-19 response.</jats:p>",
